---
import BaseLayout from '../components/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | WasteWise">
	<section class="simple-section privacy-section">
		<h1 class="simple-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
		<p class="simple-subtitle">Last updated: 2 April 2026</p>

		<div class="privacy-content">
			<p class="privacy-intro">
				WasteWise is an educational website designed to help people learn about recycling in
				Australia. We aim to keep things simple, safe, and transparent. This Privacy Policy
				explains what information we collect, how it is used, and which third‑party services
				help us operate features like our contact form, quizzes, polls, and Find tool.
			</p>
			<p class="privacy-intro">
				We do not sell personal information, and we do not use advertising or
				tracking‑based analytics. Using our website is optional, and you may choose not to
				use features that send information to external services.
			</p>

			<h2 class="privacy-h2">1. Definitions</h2>
			<dl class="privacy-dl">
				<dt>"Personal Information"</dt>
				<dd>Any information that can reasonably identify an individual, such as an IP address when linked with other data.</dd>
				<dt>"Technical Information"</dt>
				<dd>Non‑identifying data such as browser type, device type, performance metrics, or general location based on IP.</dd>
				<dt>"Third‑Party Services"</dt>
				<dd>External tools or APIs we use to run features on the site, such as form delivery, location lookup, or analytics.</dd>
				<dt>"Find Feature"</dt>
				<dd>The tool on WasteWise that helps users identify how to recycle items based on their location.</dd>
			</dl>

			<h2 class="privacy-h2">2. Information We Collect</h2>
			<p>We collect the following information when you use our website:</p>

			<h3 class="privacy-h3">2.1 Contact Form, Quiz, and Poll</h3>
			<ul class="privacy-list">
				<li>Information you enter (e.g., your message or answers)</li>
				<li>Your IP address, used for security, spam prevention, and basic functionality</li>
			</ul>

			<h3 class="privacy-h3">2.2 Find Feature</h3>
			<ul class="privacy-list">
				<li>The location you enter (e.g., suburb or address)</li>
				<li>Your IP address (to determine your region for recycling rules)</li>
			</ul>

			<h3 class="privacy-h3">2.3 Technical Information</h3>
			<p>Collected automatically by certain services:</p>
			<ul class="privacy-list">
				<li>Browser and device details</li>
				<li>Performance metrics</li>
				<li>General region based on IP</li>
			</ul>
			<p>We do not collect personal information anywhere else on the site.</p>

			<h2 class="privacy-h2">3. How Your Information Is Processed</h2>
			<h3 class="privacy-h3">3.1 Contact Form Services</h3>
			<p>We use FormSubmit.co or Submify to deliver your message to our email inbox. These services may process:</p>
			<ul class="privacy-list">
				<li>Your form message</li>
				<li>Your IP address (for abuse prevention)</li>
			</ul>

			<h3 class="privacy-h3">3.2 Cloudflare Turnstile</h3>
			<p>Used to protect our forms from bots and spam. Cloudflare may collect:</p>
			<ul class="privacy-list">
				<li>IP address</li>
				<li>Browser details</li>
				<li>Interaction data</li>
			</ul>

			<h3 class="privacy-h3">3.3 Profanity‑Checker API</h3>
			<p>Used to filter inappropriate content in contact form messages. Only the message text is sent to this service.</p>

			<h2 class="privacy-h2">4. Find Feature (Location Search)</h2>
			<p>When you use the Find tool:</p>
			<h3 class="privacy-h3">4.1 Nominatim (OpenStreetMap)</h3>
			<p>Your entered location is sent to Nominatim to convert it into coordinates.</p>
			<h3 class="privacy-h3">4.2 RecycleMate</h3>
			<p>The converted location is sent to RecycleMate to determine correct recycling instructions.</p>
			<h3 class="privacy-h3">4.3 Leaflet</h3>
			<p>RecycleMate may use Leaflet (their map renderer) to display results.</p>
			<h3 class="privacy-h3">4.4 We do not store your location</h3>
			<p>WasteWise does not save or retain your address or coordinates.</p>

			<h2 class="privacy-h2">5. IP Lookup Services</h2>
			<p>We use the following services to determine your region and show correct recycling information:</p>
			<ul class="privacy-list">
				<li>ip-api.com</li>
				<li>ipify.com</li>
			</ul>
			<p>These services receive your IP address to return general location data (e.g., state or region).</p>

			<h2 class="privacy-h2">6. Analytics</h2>
			<p>We use Vercel Analytics and Vercel Speed Insights to understand how the site performs. These tools may collect:</p>
			<ul class="privacy-list">
				<li>IP address</li>
				<li>Browser and device type</li>
				<li>Page load times</li>
				<li>General traffic patterns</li>
			</ul>
			<p>We do not use advertising, tracking cookies, or behavioural profiling.</p>

			<h2 class="privacy-h2">7. Why We Collect Information</h2>
			<p>We collect and process information to:</p>
			<ul class="privacy-list">
				<li>Deliver your messages to us</li>
				<li>Run quizzes and polls</li>
				<li>Provide accurate recycling information</li>
				<li>Prevent spam and automated abuse</li>
				<li>Improve site performance and reliability</li>
			</ul>
			<p>We do not use your information for marketing or advertising.</p>

			<h2 class="privacy-h2">8. How Long We Keep Information</h2>
			<p>We keep IP addresses and form/quiz/poll logs only as long as needed for security and troubleshooting. After that, they are deleted automatically or removed during routine clean‑ups.</p>
			<p>We do not store location data from the Find feature.</p>

			<h2 class="privacy-h2">9. Who We Share Information With</h2>
			<p>We do not sell or share your information with advertisers or data brokers. Your data is only processed by the services listed in this policy for the purposes described.</p>

			<h2 class="privacy-h2">10. Your Choices</h2>
			<p>Using the contact form, quiz, poll, or Find feature is optional. If you prefer not to share information, you may choose not to use these features.</p>

			<h2 class="privacy-h2">11. Contact Us</h2>
			<p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle information, you can reach us through the <a href="/contact" class="privacy-link">contact form</a> on our website.</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>